    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I am Ryoma, High Prince of Hoshido, and he who inherited Raijinto. I will give my all, however dire the times.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "This realm has a beauty so different from my own Hoshido. I would like to show it to all my siblings someday.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "My retainers are Kagero and Saizo. I am fortunate to have such loyal and meticulous people in my service.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "You're always so diligent. Remember to rely on your allies for strength. And I say, think of me as a brother.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I wish we could spar with our divine weapons. But I am aware that my Raijinto is not like yours at all. I must admit, I find it a troubling concept that your weapon discharges...Heroes.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I advise you to meditate each day, <Player Name>. It quells bad thoughts and promotes the best ones.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Ah! You must be <Player Name>. I bring greetings from a friend, <Friend Name>.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "I take no pride from such gains. It is my duty.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Adequate, but I must strive for more.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I must redouble my efforts and do better.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I will always give you my all, no matter what my power.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "Care to join me for some meditation? Then close your eyes. Empty your mind. Envision a relaxing place. I am thinking of Hoshido—cherry- blossom trees in bloom...rain in the gardens...a moon on the wane. I must admit that when I've been meditating of late, I have also envisioned something new. Places from this realm...the faces of members in the Order of Heroes...and, most of all... I see you, standing on the battlefield. That image lets me achieve inner balance like no other. I hope that you would feel just the same from my presence here. One more thing—in my own kingdom, I would never pledge my katana in service to another. But here, it is my honor and my privilege to serve you to the end with my blade.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
